      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "The OP&#39;s test case calls <code>methodToTest()</code> exactly once, therefore this answer does verify that the two calls are made together. The captured <code>List&lt;String&gt; values</code> that is being asserted will only contain the two values being tested and no others. You could also add <code>assertTrue(values.size == 2)</code>. If this is what you want I would replace the 3 assertTrue statements with a single <a href=\"http://hamcrest.org/JavaHamcrest/javadoc/2.1/org/hamcrest/Matchers.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Hamcrest</a> ... <code>assertThat(values, contains(&quot;exception.message&quot;, &quot;exception.detail&quot;));</code>"
